cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the security analysis and improvement of a key exchange protocol, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The protocol also involves information theory (cs.IT) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it aims to provide secure communication between two parties. The use of certificateless cryptography and the absence of pairing suggest that the paper may also fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CE) and software engineering (cs.SE).
